    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-10-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-10-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="207" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                <head>No. 207.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Sargent</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-10-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 20,
                            1883</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Frelinghuysen telegraphed to Mr. Sargent, instructing that a thorough
                        investigation be made promptly by the nearest consuls of the origin of
                        present trichina cases reported in Germany, for the information of the
                        Commission.</p>
            </div>
